Program: Omnibus
Title: Solitude
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376m6s
Last Broadcast Date: 13 June 2001
Stories of solitary confinement in a South African prison, a climber trapped on a mountain, being a widow and a vicar concealing his sexuality. A look at the difference between being alone and loneliness. Contributors include Noel Hector and John Spelpabowski.